's an interactive visualization tool for marketing/conversion attribution models (first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, etc.).\\n\\n**The actual code attribution system** tracks how much of a commit came from the AI agent vs the human user, capturing this in checkpoint metadata and optionally in commit trailers.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Core Attribution Architecture\\n\\n### 1. **Data Collection Points**\\n\\nAttribution data is captured at **two distinct moments**:\\n\\n#### **At Prompt Start** (`CalculatePromptAttribution`)\\n- **File**: `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` (lines 377-440)\\n- **What's captured**: User edits made since the last checkpoint, BEFORE the agent runs\\n- **Data stored in `PromptAttribution` struct** (in `/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go`, lines 166-191):\\n  - `UserLinesAdded` / `UserLinesRemoved`: aggregate counts\\n  - `UserAddedPerFile`: **per-file breakdown** (map[string]int) - critical for tracking line ownership\\n  - `AgentLinesAdded` / `AgentLinesRemoved`: cumulative agent work so far\\n  - `CheckpointNumber`: which checkpoint this was recorded before\\n\\n#### **At Commit Time** (`CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated`)\\n- **File**: `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` (lines 189-357)\\n- **What's calculated**:\\n  1. Sum all accumulated user edits from all `PromptAttribution` records\\n  2. Add post-checkpoint user edits (shadow → head diff)\\n  3. Calculate agent work (base → shadow minus accumulated user edits)\\n  4. Estimate user self-modifications (LIFO: users modify their own code first)\\n  5. Compute final percentage\\n\\n### 2. **Storage in Checkpoint Metadata**\\n\\nAttribution is stored in **`InitialAttribution`** struct in `/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/checkpoint.go` (lines 490-512):\\n\\n```go\\ntype InitialAttribution struct {\\n    CalculatedAt    time.Time `json:\\\"calculated_at\\\"`\\n    AgentLines      int       `json:\\\"agent_lines\\\"`      // Lines added by agent\\n    HumanAdded      int       `json:\\\"human_added\\\"`      // Lines added by human\\n    HumanModified   int       `json:\\\"human_modified\\\"`   // Lines modified by human\\n    HumanRemoved    int       `json:\\\"human_removed\\\"`    // Lines removed by human\\n    TotalCommitted  int       `json:\\\"total_committed\\\"`  // Net additions in commit\\n    AgentPercentage float64   `json:\\\"agent_percentage\\\"` // agent_lines / total_committed * 100\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Stored at**: `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch at path `<checkpoint-id[:2]>/<checkpoint-id[2:]>/0/metadata.json` (session-specific metadata)\\n\\n### 3. **Files Touched Tracking**\\n\\n**File**: `/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` (line 111)\\n\\n```go\\nFilesTouched []string `json:\\\"files_touched,omitempty\\\"`\\n```\\n\\n- Tracks files modified/created/deleted during a session\\n- Stored in checkpoint metadata (`CommittedMetadata.FilesTouched`)\\n- Used to scope attribution calculations (only files in `filesTouched` are analyzed)\\n- **NOT line-level**: just file paths, not individual line ownership\\n\\n### 4. **The Per-File Pool Heuristic** (Most Important!)\\n\\n**Location**: `/docs/architecture/attribution.md` (lines 123-174)\\n\\nThis is the key innovation solving the core problem: **when a user modifies code, how do we know if they modified their own lines or agent lines?**\\n\\n**Solution**: Per-file ownership pools with LIFO assumption\\n```go\\n// estimateUserSelfModifications in manual_commit_attribution.go (lines 359-375)\\nfunc estimateUserSelfModifications(\\n    accumulatedUserAddedPerFile map[string]int,\\n    postCheckpointUserRemovedPerFile map[string]int,\\n) int {\\n    var selfModified int\\n    for filePath, removed := range postCheckpointUserRemovedPerFile {\\n        userAddedToFile := accumulatedUserAddedPerFile[filePath]\\n        // User can only self-modify up to what they previously added\\n        selfModified += min(removed, userAddedToFile)\\n    }\\n    return selfModified\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Why this works**:\\n- Users typically edit their own recent additions before touching agent code\\n- Avoids impossible problem of tracking individual line identity (\\\"which `}` was removed?\\\")\\n- Per-file tracking in `UserAddedPerFile` enables this heuristic\\n- Trade-off: medium accuracy, low complexity, fast performance\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Session State & Attribution Base Commit\\n\\n**File**: `/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go` (lines 46-50)\\n\\nTwo distinct base commits:\\n\\n```go\\n// BaseCommit: tracks shadow branch, moves with migration (pull/rebase)\\nBaseCommit string `json:\\\"base_commit\\\"`\\n\\n// AttributionBaseCommit: preserves original base for attribution, stable across migration\\nAttributionBaseCommit string `json:\\\"attribution_base_commit,omitempty\\\"`\\n```\\n\\nThis separation is **critical**: when user pulls and rebases (HEAD moves), `BaseCommit` updates but `AttributionBaseCommit` stays fixed so deferred condensation still calculates attribution correctly.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Diff-Level Attribution (Line-by-Line Tracking)\\n\\n**Status**: NOT implemented with full line-level blame tracking.\\n\\nThe codebase **explicitly avoids** complex approaches:\\n- ❌ Git blame against checkpoints (too expensive)\\n- ❌ Line hash tracking (ambiguous for common lines like `}`)\\n- ❌ Position-aware diff tracking (too complex)\\n- ✅ **Per-file pool heuristic** (selected: good accuracy, low complexity)\\n\\n**Granularity achieved**:\\n- File-level: which files touched\\n- Per-file aggregate: total user additions per file\\n- Not: individual line-by-line ownership tracking\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Condensation & Attribution\\n\\n**File**: `/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`\\n\\nWhen user commits:\\n1. `PostCommit` hook triggered\\n2. If session ACTIVE and files touched → `ActionCondenseIfFilesTouched`\\n3. Attribution calculated via `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated()`\\n4. Result stored in checkpoint metadata on `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\\n5. Optional: `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer added to user commit (contains checkpoint ID)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Key Files for Attribution\\n\\n| File | Purpose |\\n|------|---------|\\n| `manual_commit_attribution.go` | Core attribution calculation logic |\\n| `manual_commit_attribution_test.go` | ~1000 lines of attribution tests |\\n| `manual_commit_types.go` | `PromptAttribution`, `CondenseResult` types |\\n| `checkpoint.go` | `InitialAttribution`, `CommittedMetadata` structs |\\n| `session/state.go` | `State`, `PromptAttribution`, `AttributionBaseCommit` |\\n| `docs/architecture/attribution.md` | Full explanation of design decisions |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Example Calculation Flow\\n\\nFrom `/docs/architecture/attribution.md` (lines 221-251):\\n\\n```\\nAgent adds 10 lines to main.go\\nUser adds 5 lines to main.go (between checkpoints)\\nUser modifies 3 of their own lines (removes 3, adds 3 different)\\n\\nResult:\\n  base → shadow: 15 lines added (10 agent + 5 user)\\n  accumulatedUserAdded: 5\\n  totalAgentAdded: 10\\n  \\n  shadow → head: +3, -3 (user's modification)\\n  Per-file tracking: min(3 removed, 5 user added) = 3 = userSelfModified\\n  \\n  agentPercentage: 10/15 = 66.7%\\n  (Without per-file tracking, it would incorrectly be 46.7%)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Tests\\n\\n- **Integration**: `/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/attribution_test.go` - full workflow tests\\n- **E2E**: `/e2e/tests/attribution_test.go` - agent-created files, mixed human/AI, multi-commit\\n- **Unit**: `/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution_test.go` - diff calculation, prompt attribution\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThis codebase implements a **practical, pragmatic attribution system** that:\\n1. **Captures data at two points**: prompt start + commit time\\n2. **Tracks per-file user additions** for accurate ownership estimation\\n3. **Uses LIFO heuristic** for line-level approximation without complexity\\n4. **Stores in checkpoint metadata** (JSON on `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch)\\n5. **Avoids overkill solutions** (git blame, line hashing, position tracking)\\n6. **Accepts trade-offs** (medium accuracy vs. low complexity)\\n\\nThe system is **informational, not security-critical**, and the per-file pool approach handles the common case (users editing their own recent code) well.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: afc698f953c341c14 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 101943\\ntool_uses: 21\\nduration_ms: 47363</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"d6583738-afa1-477a-b0b4-bac272f162a7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T17:45:24.133Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"Research how human vs AI code attribution works in this codebase. Look for:\\n\\n1. The file `attribution-playground.html` in the repo root (it's untracked per git status)\\n2. Any attribution-related code - search for \\\"attribution\\\", \\\"human\\\", \\\"ai\\\" in context of code authorship tracking\\n3. How the checkpoint/session system tracks which code was written by AI vs human\\n4. How transcripts, session logs, and metadata capture authorship information\\n5. Look at the strategy code (manual_commit*.go) for how it tracks file changes and associates them with sessions\\n6. Look at how `files_touched` works in metadata\\n7. Check if there's any diff-level attribution (line-by-line tracking of human vs AI changes)\\n8. Look at the condensation process and what metadata is preserved\\n9. Check the checkpoint metadata structures for any attribution fields\\n\\nBe very thorough - search for \\\"attribution\\\", \\\"author\\\", \\\"human\\\", \\\"ai_generated\\\", \\\"files_touched\\\", \\\"FilesTouched\\\", \\\"transcript\\\", and related terms. Read relevant files to understand the full picture.\",\"agentId\":\"afc698f953c341c14\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I've completed a thorough exploration of the human vs AI 