Total work in shadow: 18 lines added\\n  \\nStep 2: Subtract accumulated user edits to agent files\\n  Agent work: 18 - 8 = 10 lines\\n\\nStep 3: shadow → head (post-checkpoint edits)\\n  User added: 3, removed: 2\\n\\nStep 4: LIFO self-modification estimate\\n  User removed 2 lines from main.go\\n  User previously added 6 to main.go\\n  Self-modified: min(2, 6) = 2\\n  Modified agent lines: 0\\n\\nStep 5: Final calculation\\n  Agent lines in commit: 10\\n  Total committed: 15\\n  Agent percentage: 66.7%\\n```\\n\\n### LIFO Heuristic Demo\\nA special interactive section where users can:\\n- See a file with mixed human (blue) and agent (green) lines\\n- Click to \\\"remove\\\" lines and see how the LIFO heuristic determines whether it was a human self-modification or an agent modification\\n- Compare \\\"with per-file tracking\\\" vs \\\"without\\\" to see why per-file pools matter\\n- Show the example from the docs: agent adds 10, user adds 5, user modifies 3 → 66.7% vs incorrect 46.7%\\n\\n### Visual Elements\\n- Color coding: blue/indigo for human, green/emerald for agent, gray for unchanged base\\n- Git-style diff visualization for each step\\n- Animated transitions between steps\\n- A \\\"shadow branch\\\" indicator showing checkpoint state vs working tree state\\n- Flow diagram matching the one in attribution.md\\n\\n### Data Flow Diagram\\nShow the three git trees and how they relate:\\n```\\nbaseTree ──────────────────────── headTree\\n    │                                │\\n    │  (agent work + user edits      │  (post-checkpoint\\n    │   captured in checkpoints)     │   user edits)\\n    │                                │\\n    └──────── shadowTree ────────────┘\\n```\\n\\n### Presets\\nInclude preset scenarios:\\n1. **Simple**: Agent writes everything, no human edits → 100%\\n2. **Mixed**: Agent and human both contribute → ~60%\\n3. **Heavy editing**: Human rewrites most of agent's code → ~20%\\n4. **Self-modification**: Human modifies own code (LIFO kic